"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887113","Home Office","false","2018-04-24","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes information on the number of persons specifically detained under section 136 of the Mental Health Act 1983, including information on where the person is detained, and whether they are under 18 or aged 18 years and over, at police force area level only.</p><p> </p><p>These data were collected on a mandatory basis for the first time in 2016/17, and are published as part of the ‘Police powers and procedures, England and Wales’ statistical bulletin, which can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2017</a></p><p> </p><p>Table MHA.05c of the accompanying data tables show that, in 2016/17, nobody was detained in a police station following a section 136 detention in the West Midlands police force area.</p><p> </p><p>Figures published by the National Police Chiefs’ Council also show that a police station was not used to detain a person under the age of 18 following a section 136 detention in any case in either 2014/15 or 2015/16. Data are not available for previous years.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-04-24T12:11:51.22Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887113/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887113/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887113/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-19","Compulsorily Detained Psychiatric Patients: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many children living in (a) the West Midlands and (b) Coventry spent time in a police station as a place of safety as a result of a mental health condition in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","136678"
