"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886349","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>This information is publically available in the statistical first release Children looked after in England including adoption 2016 to 2017 at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-looked-after-in-england-including-adoption-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-looked-after-in-england-including-adoption-2016-to-2017</a>.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-04-23T16:50:08.007Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886349/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886349/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886349/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-18","Care Leavers: Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many young people classified as homeless were previously in care in (a) the North East and (b) England.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","136544"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886350","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>On 16 March 2018, the government published data and analysis as part of the Department for Education’s Children in Need Review. This included the finding that Children in Need have worse educational outcomes than their peers from the early years, make less progress throughout school, and are more likely than other children to become a young adult who is Not in Education, Employment or Training three years after completing Key Stage 4.</p><p> </p><p>The scope of the review is focussed on educational outcomes, and we have no plans to extend this. However, we recognise that the factors affecting these children and young people’s educational outcomes, such as the support they receive, may also lead to other poorer outcomes. That is why our data publication sets out our intention to understand the lifetime outcomes of Children in Need, including exploring the feasibility of matching the Department for Education’s Children in Need data with data from other government departments.</p><p> </p><p>Children’s social care and schools have a central role in supporting Children in Need. It is therefore important for us to focus the review on what we can do now whilst making progress and working across government to understand more about other outcomes over the longer-term.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-04-23T16:55:18.8Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886350/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886350/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886350/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-18","Pupils: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether his Department's review on the educational outcomes of children in need of help or support aged 16 and 17 will consider any other outcomes where the support those children have received may cause an effect.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","136545"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886351","Department for International Trade","false","2018-04-26","<p>The UK is committed to promoting the economic empowerment of all women and recognises trade as an important lever for equality. Last week, my Rt Hon Friend, the Secretary of State for International Trade, announced that, as the UK establishes an independent trade policy, we will take a gender-responsive approach to trade and create a framework that delivers for female exporters (www.gov.uk/government/speeches/global-economic-outlook-trade-growth-and-the-commonwealth).</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-04-26T12:23:50.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886351/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886351/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886351/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-04-18","Trade Agreements: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether his Department plans to conduct impact assessments on the effect of trade deals after the UK leaves the EU on women and women's rights .","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","136546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886352","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-23","<p>Decisions about the sourcing of steel for our major procurement programmes are taken by our prime contractors, taking into account the cost, timeliness of availability and the specification of steel needed to meet the requirements of defence contracts. These considerations allow defence contractors to deliver value for money for the taxpayer, and will be finalised upon contract award.</p><p>European and UK procurement regulations do not allow the Ministry of Defence to mandate the use of specific suppliers as part of the contract.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-04-23T16:16:10.08Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886352/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886352/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886352/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-18","Royal Fleet Auxiliary","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will take steps to ensure that only British steel is used to build the three new Royal Navy support ships regardless of the outcome of the international tender.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","136547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886353","Department for Education","false","2018-04-27","<p>On 14 March, as part of the government’s Integrated Communities Strategy, we announced our intention to consult on a voluntary code of practice for out-of-school settings providers. This will set out clear standards and expectations for providers, which would include those providers operating schools outside of mainstream education, such as part-time or supplementary schools. We will invite views on the code of practice later this year.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-04-27T13:30:03.687Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886353/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886353/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886353/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-18","Alternative Education: Codes of Practice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will reassess the potential merits of requiring a code of practice for schools which operate outside mainstream education.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","136548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886354","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-25","<p>The Government remains committed to improving services on the Transpennine line. However, electrifying the line alone would not deliver the capacity and customer improvements which passengers are demanding. We are currently working with Rail North and Network Rail to develop very significant improvements for rail passengers on the route with phased introduction from December 2022. These could be the result of investment in new trains, electrification or other infrastructure work.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-04-25T14:12:10.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886354/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886354/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-18","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make it his policy to electrify the Transpennine Railway.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","136549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886355","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>Information on the number of missing incidents of looked after children in children’s homes by the location of the placement is shown in the attached table.</p><p>These statistics are experimental statistics based on data collected for the first time in 2015 and should be treated with caution as local councils’ recording of this information is improving over time. The figures are therefore not comparable between years and any assessment of trends should take this into account. The information provided does not mean that the number of children going missing is increasing in the volumes indicated in the table.</p><p>Local councils have improved their reporting of missing incidents through increased collaboration with partner organisations and carers, updated recording systems, and further training for carers to improve understanding of reporting processes.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-04-23T16:42:45.56Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886355/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886355/answer","136550_Table.pdf","136550_Table.pdf","missing_incidents_in_children’s_homes","missing_incidents_in_children’s_homes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886355/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-18","Children in Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 6 April 2018 to Question 134364, on runaway children, how many looked-after children placed in children’s homes (a) inside and (b) outside the borough of the authority responsible for their care were reported missing.","false","Biography information for Ann Coffey","Stockport","Ann Coffey","136550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886356","Home Office","false","2018-08-30","<p>My department has introduced 5 regulations as a result of EU legislation since 23 June 2016.</p><p>In 2018, we expect to introduce a further 4 regulations.</p><p>In 2019, we do not expect to introduce any regulations as a result of EU legislation. However, the exact number is subject to ongoing negotiations.</p><p>All regulations implementing EU legislation that have been introduced since 2013 and impact assessments, where available, can be found on <a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk" target="_blank">www.legislation.gov.uk</a>.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-08-30T13:54:40.83Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886356/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886356/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886356/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-18","Home Office: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, which regulations her Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate she has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886357","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-26","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office has not introduced any regulations as a result of EU legislation since 23 June 2016 and we do not expect to introduce any regulations as a result of EU legislation in 2018.</p><p>In 2019, we also do not expect to introduce any regulations as a result of EU legislation. However, the exact number is subject to ongoing negotiations.</p><p>All regulations implementing EU legislation that have been introduced since 2013 and impact assessments, where available, can be found on <a href="https://http//www.legislation.gov.uk" target="_blank">www.legislation.gov.uk</a></p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-04-26T16:41:17.413Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886357/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886357/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886357/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-18","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886358","Treasury","false","2018-04-27","<p>HM Treasury has introduced 41 regulations as a result of EU legislation since 23 June 2016.</p><p> </p><p>In 2018, we expect to introduce a further 5 regulations beyond those already laid this year.</p><p> </p><p>The number of regulations to be introduced in 2019 is subject to ongoing negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>All regulations implementing EU legislation that have been introduced since 2013 and impact assessments, where available, can be found on <a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.legislation.gov.uk</a><em>.</em></p><p> </p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-04-27T10:07:22.073Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886358/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886358/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886358/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-18","Treasury: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886359","Attorney General","false","2018-04-30","<p>The Attorney General’s Office has not made any regulations pursuant to EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to the present day, and does not expect to make regulations pursuant to EU legislation in either 2018 or 2019.</p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2018-04-30T07:37:31.473Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886359/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886359/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886359/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-04-18","Attorney General: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136554"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886360","Cabinet Office","false","2018-05-22","<p>My department have introduced no regulations as a result of EU Legislation since 23 June 2016.</p><p> </p><p>In 2018, we expect to introduce 6 regulations.</p><p> </p><p>In 2019, we expect to introduce 3 regulations. However, the exact number is subject to ongoing negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>All regulations relating to EU legislation that have been introduced since 2013 and impact assessments, where available, can be found on <a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk" target="_blank">www.legislation.gov.uk</a></p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-05-22T16:26:55.293Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886360/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886360/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886360/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-04-18","Cabinet Office: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886361","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-01","<p>All regulations implementing EU legislation that have been introduced since 2013 can be found on <a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.legislation.gov.uk</a>. Impact assessments, where available, can also be found here which provide details of costs of the implemented regulations.</p><p> </p><p>In 2018, we expect to introduce a further 6 regulations. In 2019, we expect to introduce 6 regulations. However, the exact number is subject to ongoing negotiations.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-05-01T17:01:49.547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886361/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886361/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886361/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-18","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136556"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886362","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-04-27","<p>My department has introduced eight regulations as a result of EU legislation since 23 June 2016.</p><p> </p><p>In 2018, we expect to introduce one further regulation.</p><p> </p><p>In 2019, we expect to introduce one regulation. However, the exact number is subject to ongoing negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>All regulations implementing EU legislation that have been introduced since 2013 and impact assessments, where available, can be found on www.legislation.gov.uk.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-04-27T10:19:50.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886362/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886362/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886362/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-18","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136557"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886363","Department for Education","false","2018-04-27","<p>The department introduced The Education (School Teachers’ Qualifications and Induction Arrangements and Special Educational Needs Co-ordinators) (Amendment) Regulations 2016, which came into force on 17 November 2016.</p><p>These regulations give effect to the requirement to allow partial access to the teaching profession (partial Qualified Teacher Status) by reference to the relevant provisions in the European Union (Recognition of Professional Qualifications) Regulations 2015 (S.I. 2015/2059).</p><p>The department anticipate negligible costs associated with these changes.</p><p>The department introduced the European Union (Recognition of Professional Qualifications) (Amendment) Regulations 2016 (S.I. 2016/1094) which came into force in December 2016.</p><p>The purpose of this legislation was to ensure the requirements of the revised Mutual Recognition of Professional Qualifications (MRPQ) Directive 2005/36/EC (PQD) were met. This Statutory Instrument added three early years professions to the main MRPQ implementing regulations, allowing for the mutual recognition of these qualifications within the European Union.</p><p>There are currently no direct costs to the private sector or public purse as a result of these regulations.</p><p>Should any subsequent changes be required to the MRPQ regulations, the department will accordingly amend its regulations to reflect the necessary changes</p><p> </p><p>.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-04-27T09:45:01.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886363/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886363/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886363/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-18","Department for Education: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136558"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886364","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-25","<p>A total of 14 of regulations have been introduced in England as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016. Impact assessments were required for two of these regulations which together provide an estimated direct annual net cost to business of £560,000. A list of the regulations including those with impact assessments is provided below.</p><p> </p><p>A total of six EU directives are currently expected to require domestic legislation by Defra before we leave the EU on 29 March 2019. Assuming we continue to transpose EU law during the envisaged implementation period, we are currently aware of a further five EU regulations that would require domestic legislation before the end of 2019. A list of the EU regulations concerned is also provided below.</p><p> </p><p>List of EU related regulations introduced since June 2016</p><p> </p><p>1. The Waste (Meaning of Recovery) (Miscellaneous Amendments) Regulations 2016</p><p> </p><p>2. The Forest Law Enforcement, Governance and Trade (Amendment) Regulations 2016</p><p> </p><p>3. The Single Common Market Organisation (Emergency Aid for Milk Producers) (Amendment) Regulations 2016</p><p> </p><p>4. The Producer Responsibility Obligations (Packaging Waste) (Amendment) Regulations 2016</p><p> </p><p>5. The Detergents (Amendment) Regulations 2016</p><p> </p><p>6. The Plant Health (Fees) (England) (Amendment) Regulations 2016</p><p> </p><p>7. The Plant Health (England) (Amendment) Order 2017</p><p> </p><p>8. The Water Resources (Environmental Impact Assessment) (England and Wales) (Amendment) Regulations 2017</p><p> </p><p>9. The Environmental Impact Assessment (Land Drainage Improvement Works) (Amendment) Regulations 2017</p><p> </p><p>10.The Environmental Impact Assessment (Forestry) (England and Wales) (Amendment) Regulations 2017</p><p> </p><p>11.The Environmental Impact Assessment (Agriculture) (England) (No. 2) (Amendment) Regulations 2017</p><p> </p><p>12.The Marketing of Fruit Plant and Propagating Material (England) Regulations 2017</p><p> </p><p>13.The Single Common Market Organisation (Emergency Aid) (England and Northern Ireland) Regulations 2017</p><p> </p><p>14.The Common Agricultural Policy (Control and Enforcement, Cross-Compliance, Scrutiny of Transactions and Appeals) (Amendment) (England) Regulations 2017</p><p> </p><p>List of EU Directives due to be transposed by March 2019</p><p> </p><p>1. Directive (EU) 2016/2284 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 14 December 2016 on the reduction of national emissions of certain atmospheric pollutants, amending Directive 2003/35/EC and repealing Directive 2001/81/EC.</p><p> </p><p>2. COMMISSION DIRECTIVE (EU) 2017/2096 of 15 November 2017 amending Annex II to Directive 2000/53/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council on end-of life vehicles.</p><p> </p><p>3. COMMISSION IMPLEMENTING DIRECTIVE (EU) 2018/100 of 22 January 2018 amending Directives 2003/90/EC and 2003/91/EC setting out implementing measures for the purposes of Article 7 of Council Directive 2002/53/EC and Article 7 of Council Directive 2002/55/EC respectively, as regards the characteristics to be covered as a minimum by the examination and the minimum conditions for examining certain varieties of agricultural plant species and vegetable species.</p><p> </p><p>4. Commission Implementing Directive (EU) 2018/484 of 21 March 2018 amending Directive 93/49/EEC as regards requirements to be fulfilled by the propagating material of certain genera or species of Palmae in respect of Rhynchophorus ferrugineus (Olivier).</p><p> </p><p>5. Commission Directive (EU) 2015/996 of 19 May 2015 establishing common noise assessment methods according to Directive 2002/49/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council.</p><p> </p><p>6. Commission Directive (EU) 2017/845 of 17 May 2017 amending Directive 2008/56/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council as regards the indicative lists of elements to be taken into account for the preparation of marine strategies.</p><p> </p><p>List of EU Directives with transposition dates between April and December 2019</p><p> </p><p>1. DIRECTIVE (EU) 2017/2102 OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND OF THE COUNCIL of 15 November 2017 amending Directive 2011/65/EU on the restriction of the use of certain hazardous substances in electrical and electronic equipment.</p><p> </p><p>2. Commission Directive (EU) 2018/350 of 8 March 2018 amending Directive 2001/18/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council as regards the environmental risk assessment of genetically modified organisms.</p><p> </p><p>3. Directive (EU) 2018/410 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 14 March 2018 amending Directive 2003/87/EC to enhance cost-effective emission reductions and low-carbon investments, and Decision (EU) 2015/1814.</p><p> </p><p>4. Council Directive (EU) 2017/159 of 19 December 2016 implementing the Agreement concerning the implementation of the Work in Fishing Convention, 2007 of the International Labour Organisation, concluded on 21 May 2012 between the General Confederation of Agricultural Cooperatives in the European Union (Cogeca), the European Transport Workers' Federation (ETF) and the Association of National Organisations of Fishing Enterprises in the European Union.</p><p> </p><p>5. Council Directive (EU) 2018/131 of 23 January 2018 implementing the Agreement concluded by the European Community Shipowners' Associations (ECSA) and the European Transport Workers' Federation (ETF) to amend Directive 2009/13/EC in accordance with the amendments of 2014 to the Maritime Labour Convention, 2006, as approved by the International Labour Conference on 11 June 2014.</p><p> </p><p><strong><br> </strong></p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-04-25T14:26:48.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886364/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886364/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886364/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-18","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136559"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886365","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-04-26","<p>My department has not introduced any regulations as a result of EU legislation. We do not expect to make any regulations as a result of EU legislation in 2018 and 2019, however, this will be dependent on negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Fareham","Suella Braverman",,"2018-04-26T15:48:35.623Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886365/answer","Biography information for Suella Braverman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886365/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886365/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-04-18","Department for Exiting the European Union: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136560"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886366","Department for International Development","false","2018-04-25","<p>DFID has not introduced any regulations as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and does not plan to implement any regulations as a result of EU legislation in 2018 or 2019.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-04-25T16:28:23.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886366/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886366/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886366/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-04-18","Department for International Development: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, which regulations her Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate she has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886367","Department for International Trade","false","2018-04-27","<p>As a result of EU obligations, the department has made nine statutory instruments since the referendum and currently anticipates that we will make another ten instruments, to implement EU obligations between now and the end of 2019.</p><p>These nineteen instruments fall into two groups: regulations to implement export controls and regulations to ratify trade agreements which the EU will conclude while the UK remains a member.</p><p>As yet, no estimate has been made of the cost of each regulation. This is either because i) the regulations are not due to come into force until 2019 or ii) the impact of the regulations is minimal and therefore, no assessment is required.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-04-27T11:17:43.613Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886367/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886367/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-04-18","Department for International Trade: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886368","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-26","<p>My department has introduced 32 regulations as a result of EU legislation since 23 June 2016.</p><p> </p><p>In 2018, we expect to introduce a further 11 regulations.</p><p> </p><p>In 2019, we expect to introduce 7 regulations. However, the exact number is subject to ongoing negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>All regulations implementing EU legislation that have been introduced since 2013 and impact assessments, where available, can be found on <a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk" target="_blank">www.legislation.gov.uk</a>.</p><p> </p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-04-26T11:18:48.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886368/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886368/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-18","Department for Transport: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886369","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-26","<p>The UK remains a member of the EU until we leave, with full rights and obligations of membership. This includes transposing EU legislation into UK law.</p><p> </p><p>As such, the legislation which has been or will be brought forward by DWP as a result of the following EU legislation since 23 June 2016 is listed below:</p><p> </p><p>1) Directive (EU) 2013/59/Euratom lays down basic safety standards for protection against the dangers arising from exposure to ionising radiation and came into force 1 January 2018. The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy has the overall UK government policy lead. The Health and Safety Executive is responsible for a discrete set of regulations (The Ionising Radiations Regulations 2017/1075) under the Basic Safety Standards Directive. The full impact assessment is available at the following link: <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2017/1075/impacts" target="_blank">https://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2017/1075/impacts</a></p><p> </p><p>2) Directive (EU) 2017/164 establishing a fourth list of indicative occupational exposure limit values pursuant to Council Directive 98/24/EC. The transposition deadline is 21 August 2018. The full impact assessment is available at the following link: <a href="http://www.hse.gov.uk/consult/condocs/cd283.htm" target="_blank">http://www.hse.gov.uk/consult/condocs/cd283.htm</a></p><p> </p><p>3) Directive (EU) 2016/2341 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 14 December 2016 on the activities and supervision of institutions for occupational retirement provision (IORPs). The transposition deadline is 13 January 2019. We are engaging closely with industry and will assess any cost or impact of any amendments to existing legislation as appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>Any transposition of EU legislation beyond 29 March 2019 will be dependant on the outcome of on-going negotiations with the EU on the UK’s relationship with the EU following our exit from the EU.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-04-26T14:07:34.263Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886369/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886369/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-18","Department for Work and Pensions: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, which regulations her Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate she has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886370","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-27","<p>The Department has introduced 15 regulations as a result of European Union legislation since 23 June 2016 to date. In 2018, we expect to introduce a further three regulations. In 2019, we currently do not expect to introduce any regulations. However, the exact number is subject to ongoing negotiations. All regulations implementing EU legislation that have been introduced since 2013 and impact assessments, where available, can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk" target="_blank">www.legislation.gov.uk</a></p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-04-27T12:53:42.413Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886370/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886370/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886370/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-18","Department of Health and Social Care: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886371","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-25","<p>The Ministry of Defence has not introduced any regulations as a result of EU legislation since 23 June 2016 and currently has no plans to implement any regulations as a result of EU legislation in 2018 and 2019.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-04-25T16:18:40.21Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886371/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886371/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886371/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-18","Ministry of Defence: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136566"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886372","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-27","<p>My Department has introduced four regulations as a result of EU legislation since 23 June 2016.</p><p>We do not expect to introduce any regulations as a result of EU legislation in 2018.</p><p>We have no current plans to introduce any regulations as a result of EU legislation in 2019. However, the exact number is subject to on-going negotiations.</p><p>Impact assessments for all regulations implementing EU legislation, where available, can be found on www.legislation.gov.uk</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-04-27T13:13:11.927Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886372/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886372/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886372/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-18","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886373","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>In 2015 and 2016 the Department signed five PF2 contracts and the names and addresses of the 46 schools in these contracts are given in the attached annex.</p><p> </p><p>Prior to these PF2 contracts, between 1997 and 2013, 169 contracts were signed by local authorities under the private finance initiative. Whilst the Department holds a list of these contracts, which is published by Her Majesty’s Treasury, it does not maintain a list of the individual schools within these contracts. Local authorities will hold this information.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-04-23T16:07:47.203Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886373/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886373/answer","PF2_Contracts_2015-2016.xls","PF2_Contracts_2015-2016.xls","PF2_contracts_2015-2016.","PF2_contracts_2015-2016.","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886373/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-18","Schools: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the names and addresses are of all schools in England and Wales which have been constructed via a private finance initiative or PF2 programme.","false","Biography information for Stella Creasy","Walthamstow","Stella Creasy","136568"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886374","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-27","<p>My department has not introduced any regulations as a result of EU legislation since 23</p><p>June 2016.</p><p> </p><p>In 2018, we do not expect to introduce further regulations.</p><p>In 2019, we expect to introduce one regulation. However, the exact number is subject to ongoing negotiations and the financial impact is unknown at this time.</p><p> </p><p>All regulations implementing EU legislation that have been introduced since 2013 and impact assessments, where available, can be found on <a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk" target="_blank">www.legislation.gov.uk</a>.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-04-27T13:50:25.473Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886374/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886374/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886374/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-18","Ministry of Justice: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136569"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886375","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-04-27","<p>My Department has not introduced any regulations as a result of EU legislation since 23 June 2016.</p><p>We do not expect to introduce any regulations as a result of EU legislation in 2018 and 2019.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2018-04-27T11:16:14.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886375/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886375/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886375/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-04-18","Northern Ireland Office: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, which regulations her Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate she has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136570"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886376","Scotland Office","false","2018-04-25","<p>Since 23 June 2016, my Department has not been responsible for introducing any regulations as a result of EU legislation.</p><p>I do not currently anticipate that my department will be required to implement regulations in future as a result of EU legislation.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-04-25T11:48:35.217Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886376/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886376/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886376/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-04-18","Scotland Office: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, which regulations his Department (a) has introduced as a result of EU legislation from 23 June 2016 to date and (b) expects to implement as a result of EU legislation in (i) 2018 and (ii) 2019; and what estimate he has made of the cost of each such regulation to the (A) public purse and (B) private sector.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","136571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886377","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-04-27","<p>We are considering the recommendations in the Full Time Social Action Review’s report, including the recommendation regarding the establishment of a ministerial group. The Government Response to the Review’s report will be published in due course.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-04-27T10:27:26.973Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886377/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886377/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886377/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-18","Young People: Voluntary Work","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to the Independent review of Full-Time Social Action, published in January 2018, what plans his Department has to establish a Ministerial group on youth full-time social action.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","136572"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886378","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-27","<p>The UK has a strong track record in developing design and civil engineering standards, both at home and abroad. We have been at the forefront of improving standards, with those that originated from our own national bodies being adopted the world over in a wide range of sectors. We will continue to work with other European countries, and globally, to drive new standards after we leave the EU.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-04-27T11:07:41.713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886378/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886378/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886378/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-18","Construction: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what plans his Department has to ensure that design and civil engineering standards are maintained after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","136573"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886379","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-04-27","<p>The NCS Trust’s online Opportunity Hub matches young people who have graduated from the NCS programme to further opportunities, including full time social action opportunities.</p><p> </p><p>DCMS is carefully considering the recommendations made by the recently published independent Review of Full Time Social Action by Young People and will respond in due course.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-04-27T10:28:30.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886379/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886379/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-18","Young People: Voluntary Work","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether his Department has plans to make an assessment of the effect of participation in National Citizen Service on the level of young people taking part in youth full-time social action.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","136574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886380","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-26","<p>The Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government has already secured additional flexibility to retain income at Autumn Budget to deliver across our agenda, including EU exit. Departmental allocations for 2019-20 will be agreed later in 2018, as requirements will be affected by progress in negotiations with the EU.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-04-26T15:41:04.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886380/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886380/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886380/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-18","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether he has discussed with the Chancellor of the Exchequer additional funding for any projects relating to the UK leaving the EU over the next five years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","136575"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886381","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-23","<p>In England, the European Regional Development Fund (ERDF) and European Social Fund (ESF) are collectively known as the Structural Funds. MHCLG are responsible for managing the England ERDF programme and DWP the ESF programme. For the 2014-20 programming period the majority of the Structural Funds have been notionally allocated to Local Enterprise Partnership areas. These allocations were announced by the Secretary of State for Business on 17 April 2014. The letter notifying Local Enterprise Partnership Chairs and MPs of the allocations can be found here: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-04-23T15:23:42.733Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886381/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886381/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886381/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-18","Local Government Finance: EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will publish the level of funding allocated to local authorities through the (a) European Regional Development Fund and (b) European Social Fund.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","136576"
