"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886384","Treasury","false","2018-04-25","<p>Providing support for a maximum of two children in tax credits and Universal Credit is about ensuring those who receive income related benefits face the same financial choices as those supporting themselves solely through work. The government also recognises that some claimants are not able to make the same choices about the number of children in their family and consequently has provided exceptions in certain cases, including in cases of non-consensual conception.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics relating to the operation of the policy and the exceptions will be published in due course, once there are sufficient cases to enable robust analysis and the data has been quality assured.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-04-25T13:22:47.703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886384/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886384/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886384/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-18","Child Tax Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many claims have been made under the non-consensual conception exemption for child tax credit in (a) Scotland, (b) England, (c) Wales and (d) Northern Ireland since 6 April 2017.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","136579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886385","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-26","<p>The non-consensual conception exemption has only been in operation since last April. Statistics relating to the operation of the policy and the exceptions will be published in due course, once there are sufficient cases to enable robust analysis and the data has been quality assured.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-04-26T13:41:09.09Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886385/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886385/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886385/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-18","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claims have been made under the non-consensual conception exemption for the child element of universal credit in (a) Scotland, (b) England, (c) Wales and (d) Northern Ireland since 6 April 2017.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","136580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886386","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>I can confirm that the then Prime Minister David Cameron wrote to Prime Minister Modi on 17 June 2016. The letter covered a range of issues on which the British Government was engaging the Indian Government at the time, including extradition. I can also confirm the then Prime Minister did raise Michelle Samaraweera's case with Prime Minister Modi.</p><p>I can assure the Hon Lady that the British Government has continued to press the Indian Government to accelerate Mr Vyas' extradition hearing. Our High Commission officials raised this point with the Indian Government most recently in the margins of the latest hearing on 16 April.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-04-23T16:45:35.46Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886386/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886386/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886386/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-18","Michelle Samaraweera","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will place in the Library a copy of the letter that the Prime Minister sent to the Prime Minister of India on the extradition of the person who killed Michelle Samaraweera referred to in his Department's letter of 8 September 2016 to the hon. Member for Walthamstow.","false","Biography information for Stella Creasy","Walthamstow","Stella Creasy","136581"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886387","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Government’s careers strategy, published in December 2017, aims to give young people from all backgrounds the opportunity to learn from employers about work and the skills that are valued in the workplace.</p><p> </p><p>The Careers &amp; Enterprise Company’s network of Enterprise Advisers are senior business volunteers who help schools to work with local businesses. The network is already operating in over half of secondary schools and colleges, and will be available to all of them by 2020.</p><p> </p><p>There are a number of opportunities for pupils to develop entrepreneurial skills. The new Business GCSE, which was first taught from 2017, is intended to enable students to develop as commercially minded and enterprising individuals. In 2014, for the first time, financial literacy was made statutory within the national curriculum as part of the citizenship curriculum for 11 to 16 year olds. Schools are free to cover enterprise and entrepreneurship teaching within their personal, social, health and economic education.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-04-23T16:01:05.807Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886387/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886387/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-18","Business: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps his Department is taking to promote entrepreneurship in schools.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","136582"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886388","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>The National Plan for Music Education sets out a vision for schools and education organisations to drive excellence in music education: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-importance-of-music-a-national-plan-for-music-education" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-importance-of-music-a-national-plan-for-music-education</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Education is providing £150 million in funding over the next two years for music education hubs to augment and support music teaching in schools so that more children can be offered the experience of a combination of classroom teaching, instrumental and vocal tuition. Music education hubs draw in the expertise of a range of education and arts organisations, such as local orchestras, ensembles, charities and other music groups.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-04-23T16:28:31.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886388/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886388/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-18","Music: Primary Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans his Department has to improve the level and availability of music education in primary schools.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","136583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886389","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring that all disabled people, including those with visual impairments, have the same access to transport and opportunities to travel as everyone else.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Department’s draft Accessibility Action Plan, published for consultation last year, set out a number of steps that are being taken in pursuit of this goal across the different transport modes. The consultation received over 1,000 responses which the Department is taking into account as it finalises a new Inclusive Transport Strategy, which will be published in due course.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-04-23T16:25:57.077Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886389/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886389/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-18","Public Transport: Visual Impairment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to support visually impaired people in using public transport.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","136584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886390","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>We are working with our UN Security Council partners to ensure that the mandate of the UN Mission for the Referendum in Western Sahara (MINURSO) continues to enable it to promote peace and security in Western Sahara. We have consistently supported language in the relevant UN Security Council resolutions to encourage the parties to continue their efforts to enhance the promotion and protection of human rights in Western Sahara.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-04-23T14:15:19.007Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886390/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886390/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-18","Western Sahara: Peacekeeping Operations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will help ensure the UN peacekeeping mission to Western Sahara is given a mandate to monitor and report on human rights abuses in the region at the next meeting of the UN Security Council.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","136585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886391","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>We do not consider that Western Sahara is occupied; we consider that its status is undetermined. We look to all parties in Western Sahara, including businesses, to conduct their activities in accordance with international law, respecting the interests of the people of Western Sahara. I discussed with the Moroccan Foreign Minister, Mr Nasser Bourita, in January the UK's desire for a lasting and mutually acceptable solution to the dispute over Western Sahara that provides for the self-determination of the people of the territory.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-04-23T14:17:29.61Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886391/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886391/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-18","Western Sahara: Natural Resources","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his Moroccan counterpart on the extraction of natural resources from occupied Western Sahara.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","136586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886392","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>We are working with our UN Security Council partners to support the UN-led process to reach a solution to the dispute over Western Sahara. The UK wants to see a lasting and mutually acceptable solution that provides for the self-determination of the people of Western Sahara. It is for the parties to the dispute to agree a solution.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-04-23T14:19:04.563Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886392/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886392/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-18","Western Sahara: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if his officials will call for a date to be set for a free and fair referendum to be carried out in Western Sahara at the next meeting of the UN Security Council.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","136587"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886393","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>The government believes that employers are best placed to advise on the knowledge, skills and behaviours needed to succeed in their industries. That is why T levels are being designed by panels of employers and industry experts to ensure that students come away with the skills that businesses are looking for. We also held a Skills Summit in November last year where over 100 employers signed a Statement of Action to commit to providing opportunities for young people to develop their skills.</p><p> </p><p>In particular, we are talking to employers about how we can best support them to deliver work placements as part of T levels. For example, we have commissioned a research project interviewing employers about their capacity and demand to offer T level work placements. We have also engaged with over 1000 employers through the work placement pilots, who are now offering work placements to students in the 17/18 academic year. A large proportion of responses to the recent consultation on T level implementation were from employer representative organisations – and we will publish the government response to this in due course.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-04-23T16:51:29.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886393/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886393/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-18","T-levels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent discussions (a) he and (b) the Minister of State for Apprenticeships and Skills have had with businesses to understand the level of demand for T Levels from employers.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","136588"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886394","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Education and Skills Funding Agency, through employers' digital accounts in the Apprenticeship Service, have paid £170 million between 6 May 2017 and the end of March 2018. We publish statistics on commitments to date on our website GOV.UK. These can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/apprenticeship-and-levy-statistics-april-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/apprenticeship-and-levy-statistics-april-2018</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Information on committed spend for future training of apprentices is not published as although there are commitments in the system in line with expected spend requirements, there are a number of reasons why these forecasts may change.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-04-23T16:01:36.763Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886394/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886394/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886394/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-18","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate he has made of the proportion apprenticeship levy that has (a) been taken from employers’ digital accounts to pay for apprenticeships and (b) been defined as committed spend for future training of apprentices.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","136589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886395","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>T levels are rigorous, technical study programmes at level 3, designed by employers to meet their skills needs. Their central purpose is to enable students to progress to skilled employment at level 3 and above, and into further relevant training at level 4, 5 or 6, either in the workplace or at an education provider</p><p> </p><p>It is too early in the development of T level programmes to identify the proportion of students who will progress to employment, higher education or apprenticeships. We are working closely with employers and higher education providers to ensure that T levels support progression to skilled employment and higher levels of technical education.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-04-23T16:52:25.13Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886395/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886395/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886395/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-18","T-levels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate he has made of the proportion of students completing T levels who will go on to (a) employment, (b) higher education and (c) apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","136590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886396","Home Office","false","2018-04-24","<p>The Government received over 50,000 representations from members of the public about the review of the regulations of air weapons, a significant proportion of which were concerned about the use of these weapons against animals such as cats. We are considering the representations that we received and will publish our findings in due course.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-04-24T09:42:03.267Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886396/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886396/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-18","Airguns","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many of the responses it received to its consultation on the use of air weapons raised concerns about the shooting of animals.","false","Biography information for Maria Caulfield","Lewes","Maria Caulfield","136591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886397","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-23","<p>During 2017/18, NHS England commissioned 113 new child and adolescent mental health services in-patient beds. The revenue funding required to support these beds was allocated during 2017/18 and 2018/19.</p><p> </p><p>There are plans to commission around 100 further new beds over the next six months, from April 2018. The revenue will be allocated on a phased basis as the beds open.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-04-23T13:48:26.943Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886397/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886397/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-18","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what the timetable is for the funding allocated to CAHMS by NHS England in January 2018 for over 130 new CAHMS beds to be released.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","136592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886398","Home Office","false","2018-04-24","<p>Information relating to the proceedings of Inter-Ministerial Groups, including minutes of their proceedings, is not disclosed as to do so could harm the frankness and candour of internal discussion.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-04-24T15:35:03.36Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886398/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/886398/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-18","Migrants' Access to Benefits and Public Services Inter-ministerial Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will publish the minutes of the Inter-Ministerial Group on Migrants' Access to Benefits and Public Services for the period between its establishment and the 2015 general election.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","136593"
